Trading Bot — Project Knowledge
This document is the single source of truth for the BTC/ETH daily trend-following
trading bot. It records the validated strategy, the locked parameters, what has and
hasn't been tested, the code architecture, and the known risks. Read this before
proposing any change.

1. What this project is
A daily (1-day candle) trend-following bot for crypto, long-only, no leverage.
It holds BTC (or ETH, run separately) when trend + momentum align, sizes the
position by volatility targeting, and exits on an ATR trailing stop. The goal is
to beat buy-and-hold on BOTH return and drawdown, not to maximise raw return.
Capital base for sizing/backtests: EUR 1,000.

2. The strategy (exact rules)
Run once per day, shortly after the daily candle closes (00:00 UTC).
ENTRY (only when flat):

close > TEMA(120)  AND
CMO(14) > 10
Position size = volatility-targeted fraction of equity (see below), set ONCE at
entry and held for the whole trade. No daily rebalancing.

EXIT (only when in position):

ATR trailing stop. Stop = highest_close_since_entry - 3.5 * ATR(14).
The stop only ratchets up, never down.
Exit when close <= stop.

POSITION SIZING (volatility targeting):

vol_ann = realized_vol_30d * sqrt(365)  (std of daily returns, annualised)
fraction = clip(0.40 / vol_ann, 0.10, 1.00)
0.40 is the target-vol level. Cap at 1.00 means NO leverage. Floor 0.10 keeps a
minimum stake.
Intuition: in high-vol crashes exposure shrinks (~33%), in calm trends it goes
to 100%.

EXECUTION ASSUMPTIONS (backtest):

Fees 0.2% per side, slippage 0.1% on stop exits. These are conservative vs OKX
spot taker fees, on purpose.


