5. Known caveats and risk numbers (be honest about these)

Vol-targeting params (40%, 30d) were tuned on the same history they were tested on
— weaker than the TEMA/ATR validation. The REAL test is forward/live data.
5% worst-case bootstrap max drawdown = -78.4%. Deeper than any single historical
drawdown. Size live capital so this is a setback, not a catastrophe.
BTC 2023-2026 was a favourable regime. No test in a prolonged sideways/bear market.
Backtest executes signal + fill at the same daily close (slightly optimistic vs
next-open).
~40 trades is a small sample; bootstrap intervals are wide.
The OkxBroker order/balance code has NOT been tested against the live OKX API yet
(no keys/network during build). Expect to refine it on OKX demo first.


6. Code architecture
The core idea: identical bot logic for paper / demo / live; only the broker differs.
tema-bot/
  config.py        all settings via .env (code and secrets separated)
  indicators.py    TEMA/CMO/ATR/realized_vol — MUST exactly match the backtest
  strategy.py      pure decide() -> ENTER / EXIT / HOLD (no IO, unit-testable)
  okx_client.py    OKX REST for SPOT: candles (paginated), ticker, balance, orders, fills
  broker.py        PaperBroker (local sim) and OkxBroker (demo/live, real fill/fee data)
  storage.py       state.json (position + equity) + trades.csv + cross-process lock
  bot.py           orchestration: `once` (systemd timer) / `run` (loop) / `stop`
  telegram_bot.py  notify() on trade events + whitelisted command listener
                   (/status /trades /equity /off /on /stop=panic exit)
  status_cli.py    quick view of state + last trades
  tests/           parity vs backtest notebook, full backtest replay through
                   decide(), strategy/broker/telegram unit tests (30 tests)
  deploy/          systemd units (daily timer + telegram listener) + install.sh
Critical invariants:

Indicator formulas in indicators.py are verified bit-for-bit identical to the
backtest (TEMA via ewm adjust=False; CMO via rolling SUM; ATR via rolling MEAN;
vol via pct_change rolling std). Changing a formula = trading a different system.
strategy.decide() follows the backtest ordering: when in position, FIRST check
exit against yesterday's stop, THEN ratchet the trailing stop for tomorrow.
Bot is idempotent on last_bar_ts: it never trades twice on the same candle.
Safety gates: OkxBroker refuses live unless ALLOW_LIVE=1, and stops if equity
exceeds MAX_LIVE_EQUITY.

Candles: use OKX bar 1Dutc; only act on CONFIRMED (closed) candles (confirm==1).
Warmup: ewm(adjust=False) is start-dependent. HIST_BARS=1200 (measured: 400 bars
gives ~$118 TEMA error vs the backtest's full history; 1200 gives <$0.001 and an
identical entry signal over the last 365 days — see tests/test_parity.py).

